21:40.833 --> 21:42.967
- All right, I'm with ya.

21:45.937 --> 21:49.006
- So how's my grandson doin'?

21:50.776 --> 21:53.878
- Hey.

21:55.080 --> 21:56.080
Hello!

21:56.082 --> 21:57.748
How's my grandson?

21:59.685 --> 22:00.551
- Doin' good, grandpa.

22:00.553 --> 22:02.320
Just stayin' busy.

22:02.322 --> 22:04.522
School, studyin', dancin'.

22:05.357 --> 22:07.024
Same ol', same ol'.

22:07.026 --> 22:08.826
- Well, there ya go.

22:11.363 --> 22:14.865
So how's the butcher
business, Dr. scalpel?

22:14.867 --> 22:16.100
- Same ol'.

22:17.870 --> 22:19.470
Oh, here they go.

22:20.405 --> 22:21.405
How cute.

22:22.074 --> 22:24.008
Did she end up with a unitard?

22:24.010 --> 22:26.510
- Ha, that'll clear a room.

22:27.380 --> 22:28.380
- Stop it.

22:29.614 --> 22:31.582
- We're just gonna order pizza.

22:31.584 --> 22:33.050
- You just went to the store.

22:34.454 --> 22:35.953
- I just thought that it would
be easier.

22:35.955 --> 22:35.953
- Nuh-nuh-nuh-nuh-no.

22:35.955 --> 22:38.589
Once everyone's here, we're not
leaving.

22:38.591 --> 22:39.790
- Why don't you come on out and
show me

22:39.792 --> 22:43.060
where we're gonna have that
portrait, huh?

22:43.062 --> 22:45.996
- Check the lighting, honey.

22:45.998 --> 22:47.465
Whew.

22:47.467 --> 22:48.467
- Yeah.

22:51.103 --> 22:52.036
- Whoo.

22:52.038 --> 22:55.406
I don't think there's enough
whiskey in all of Ireland

22:55.408 --> 22:56.741
to get through this weekend.

22:56.743 --> 22:57.742
- Forget Ireland.

22:57.744 --> 22:59.410
Check the trunk of my car.

22:59.412 --> 23:00.478
- Thank you.

23:00.480 --> 23:04.415
- Bless me.

23:16.762 --> 23:18.562
- Oh, it is so beautiful.

23:18.564 --> 23:19.564
- Yeah.

23:21.466 --> 23:25.169
I thought the same thing the
first time I came out here.

23:25.171 --> 23:28.639
- You know who I think is the
most excited about being here?

23:28.641 --> 23:29.507
- Hm?

23:29.509 --> 23:30.841
- Your granddad.

23:32.077 --> 23:33.978
He rushed around the house
trying to find

23:33.980 --> 23:35.913
his captain's uniform.

23:37.783 --> 23:39.950
For the portrait, you know.

23:39.952 --> 23:40.851
Is that all right?

23:40.853 --> 23:44.054
- Absolutely.

23:44.056 --> 23:45.656
Is he doin' okay?

23:46.925 --> 23:47.792
- Yeah.

23:47.794 --> 23:49.794
He gets tired, you know,

23:49.796 --> 23:53.431
but he still wants to
be in complete control.

23:53.433 --> 23:54.799
He sat in the backseat of the
car

23:54.801 --> 23:59.003
and he was barking
directions all the way here.

23:59.005 --> 24:02.807
He is who he is.

24:06.545 --> 24:07.545
- Mom?

24:11.183 --> 24:12.917
About this weekend.

24:15.454 --> 24:17.054
- What is it, honey?

24:17.056 --> 24:18.456
- Hey, mom.

24:18.458 --> 24:20.825
Let me get a picture of you and
Nana.

24:22.562 --> 24:23.894
- You better get my best side,
you know.

24:23.896 --> 24:27.898
- All right, make sure that
those end up in my studio.

24:27.900 --> 24:29.033
- Yes, ma'am.

24:31.637 --> 24:33.003
- You know who would have loved
it here?

24:33.005 --> 24:34.572
- Hm?

24:34.574 --> 24:36.507
- Your grandma, seana.

24:41.646 --> 24:43.781
Oh, what a terrific lady.

24:45.951 --> 24:48.853
Complicated, dressed to the
nines,

24:50.088 --> 24:51.622
but very strict.

24:52.624 --> 24:53.824
Did I ever tell you about the
time

24:53.826 --> 24:56.060
I was in the bathroom,

24:56.062 --> 24:58.496
and she walked in on me,

24:58.498 --> 25:01.699
and she yelled at me
because I wasn't sitting up

25:01.701 --> 25:03.567
straight enough on the toilet?

25:07.239 --> 25:10.774
I guess that's how she tried to
love me.

25:15.847 --> 25:16.847
- I guess.

25:23.188 --> 25:25.656
- What's the matter, honey?

25:28.560 --> 25:29.560
What is it?

25:32.865 --> 25:33.931
Sometimes...

25:35.802 --> 25:36.701
- What?

25:36.702 --> 25:40.004
- I don't feel like I belong.

25:47.145 --> 25:49.213
- I don't think you should feel
that way.

25:49.215 --> 25:53.951
I mean, we're all here because
we're connected to you.

25:53.953 --> 25:55.019
We love you.

25:59.190 --> 26:02.593
Well, I don't know what to say
except,

26:05.897 --> 26:07.097
why don't we have a drink?

26:07.099 --> 26:09.166
What do ya say?

26:09.168 --> 26:10.301
For your grandma.

26:10.303 --> 26:11.569
We'll toast.

26:49.041 --> 26:50.040
- Hey, mom!

26:50.042 --> 26:51.042
- Oh, hey!

26:55.246 --> 26:56.714
- What are you doin'?

26:56.716 --> 26:59.316
- Setting up, getting organized.

27:00.285 --> 27:01.352
Whatcha got?

27:02.754 --> 27:02.753
- Remember how you asked
everybody

27:02.755 --> 27:05.289
to bring somethin'
special for the portrait?

27:05.291 --> 27:06.291
- Mm-hmm.

27:08.026 --> 27:11.028
Aww.

27:11.030 --> 27:12.030
Wow.

27:12.864 --> 27:13.998
- Remember?

27:14.000 --> 27:16.100
- Of course I do.

27:16.102 --> 27:19.336
It's the first show I ever took
you to.

27:19.338 --> 27:21.038
- It was great, wasn't it?

27:21.040 --> 27:22.040
- Mm-hmm.

27:25.176 --> 27:27.011
- I remember thinkin'
it would be so great

27:27.013 --> 27:29.013
to learn how to dance like that.

27:29.015 --> 27:33.183
- And now you do.

27:33.185 --> 27:33.183
Wow.

27:33.185 --> 27:35.653
- Oh, we took the pictures
with 'em too, remember?

27:35.655 --> 27:36.655
- Yeah!

27:37.222 --> 27:40.324
That really is a great night.

27:40.326 --> 27:42.159
Wonderful memory.

27:42.161 --> 27:43.227
Thank you.

27:43.229 --> 27:44.328
- Thanks, mom.

27:45.297 --> 27:46.964
All right, see ya.

27:48.333 --> 27:49.333
- See ya.

28:05.250 --> 28:06.383
- Hello, sweetie.

28:06.385 --> 28:07.251
Wine?

28:07.253 --> 28:08.118
- Absolutely.

28:08.120 --> 28:09.119
- All right.

28:09.121 --> 28:10.854
Liam, drink?

28:10.856 --> 28:12.122
- Beer me!

28:12.124 --> 28:14.224
- Yes, all right.

28:14.226 --> 28:15.759
- Beer me, what?

28:16.428 --> 28:18.062
- There ya go.

28:18.064 --> 28:19.129
There ya go!

28:21.800 --> 28:22.466
- Poor baby.

28:22.468 --> 28:23.734
- Sorry.

28:23.736 --> 28:24.768
- A nice try though.

28:24.770 --> 28:27.137
- I would have given you one.

28:28.441 --> 28:31.108
- You sit down and tell
me what you've been doin'.

28:31.110 --> 28:33.777
- Well, just getting organized.

28:33.779 --> 28:36.113
- Did you get our Liam's
present?

28:36.115 --> 28:38.082
- I did, and the album?

28:38.084 --> 28:39.249
It's amazing.

28:39.251 --> 28:39.249
- Yeah.

28:39.251 --> 28:42.052
Did your mother tell you
we're planning a cruise

28:42.054 --> 28:43.353
in the fall?

28:43.355 --> 28:45.422
- No, she didn't.

28:45.424 --> 28:45.422
- Her idea.

28:45.424 --> 28:48.859
- Ugh, he sounds really
excited, doesn't he?

28:48.861 --> 28:48.859
- Mm-hmm.

28:48.861 --> 28:51.862
- It's a small boat, about 200
people.

28:51.864 --> 28:54.231
We're goin' to Alaska
before global warming

28:54.233 --> 28:56.834
destroys all the polar bears.

28:57.769 --> 28:59.336
- Mom, you don't like cold
weather.

28:59.338 --> 29:01.405
- Oh, I know, but your
daddy's gonna buy me

29:01.407 --> 29:04.074
a beautiful jacket,
aren't you, daddy dear?

29:04.076 --> 29:05.342
- Well, that's why we're goin',

29:05.344 --> 29:07.411
so she can get a new jacket.

29:07.413 --> 29:07.411
- Sounds fun, grandma.

29:07.413 --> 29:10.447
- Yeah, well, you can come along
with us

29:10.449 --> 29:12.349
if you're not in school.

29:12.351 --> 29:14.218
- I can miss school to
go see polar bears die.

29:14.220 --> 29:15.219
- No, you can't.

29:15.221 --> 29:16.186
- Dad?

29:16.188 --> 29:18.288
- No, you can't.

29:18.290 --> 29:20.357
- Oh well, we'll work on him,
okay.

29:20.359 --> 29:22.226
See if we can work it, huh?

29:22.228 --> 29:23.794
- Mmm.

29:23.796 --> 29:25.262
- If he help us to go, he
can go.

29:25.264 --> 29:26.330
- All right, stop.

29:27.266 --> 29:28.265
I wanna find out something.

29:28.267 --> 29:30.768
How did you find this place?

29:31.503 --> 29:33.003
- A friend of mine, she
works at the gallery,

29:33.005 --> 29:36.006
she's been here before, so,
yeah.

29:36.008 --> 29:36.006
- It's gorgeous.

29:36.008 --> 29:41.145
It's perfect and rustic and
great for a family gathering.

29:41.147 --> 29:42.846
And I love it.

29:42.848 --> 29:44.214
- I'll drink to that.

29:44.216 --> 29:45.256
- He'll drink to anything.

29:46.285 --> 29:47.151
- Cheers.

29:47.153 --> 29:48.153
- Oh, did we wake you up?

29:49.555 --> 29:50.420
- I'll get it.

29:50.422 --> 29:51.889
- Nuh-nuh-no.

29:51.891 --> 29:52.891
I got it.

29:55.293 --> 29:57.027
- Everybody good on drinks?

29:57.029 --> 29:58.495
- Yeah.

30:00.131 --> 30:01.198
- Hey.

30:01.200 --> 30:03.066
It's good to see you.

30:06.539 --> 30:07.539
Come on in.

30:09.974 --> 30:13.510
Um, Maggie, Aiden, you
remember my parents,

30:14.546 --> 30:18.182
and here are Francis, Liam, and
Sam.

30:18.184 --> 30:20.884
- John, Maureen.
- - Sam.

30:20.886 --> 30:22.953
- Hi.
- - Hi.

30:41.873 --> 30:45.943
- Hey, Liam baby, take a
picture of Nana for me.

30:48.147 --> 30:50.414
- Whose is that?

30:50.416 --> 30:52.049
- Yo.

30:52.051 --> 30:53.116
Yeah, just a sec.

30:53.118 --> 30:55.018
- Liam, where are you going?

30:55.020 --> 30:57.154
- Sorry, Nana, I gotta
take this.

30:57.156 --> 30:58.455
- I hate cellphones.

30:58.457 --> 30:59.990
- I am so sorry.

31:02.227 --> 31:03.627
- Hey, what's up?

31:05.263 --> 31:06.964
Yeah, we're at that house
in the middle of nowhere.

31:06.966 --> 31:08.866
My mom's painting a portrait.

31:08.868 --> 31:09.933
- Hey, Liam.

31:09.935 --> 31:11.001
- Baby, it's fine.

31:11.003 --> 31:12.603
- I guess so, sort of.

31:12.605 --> 31:14.238
Yeah, the whole family.

31:14.240 --> 31:15.639
She even brought her
real mom and stepfather.

31:15.641 --> 31:18.208
Can you believe that?

31:18.210 --> 31:20.878
I told you she was adopted.

31:20.880 --> 31:23.881
Huh, I guess you can call them
my grandparents, technically.

31:23.883 --> 31:25.315
Hadn't thought of it.

31:25.317 --> 31:27.951
Yeah, grandma and grandpa are
here.

31:27.953 --> 31:30.153
Yeah yeah, and franny.

31:32.992 --> 31:34.391
Oh no kidding, it was so ugly.

31:34.393 --> 31:35.659
They came in last night.

31:35.661 --> 31:37.461
- Smoke bothering you?

31:37.463 --> 31:39.162
- It's important to her.

31:39.164 --> 31:40.530
- Liam!

31:40.532 --> 31:43.233
Hang up the phone and get over
here.

31:43.235 --> 31:44.101
- Sam.

31:44.103 --> 31:45.202
- It's rude.

31:45.204 --> 31:46.270
- Listen, I gotta go.

31:46.272 --> 31:47.437
We're still on for tomorrow
night.

31:47.439 --> 31:49.506
Yep, yep, a'ight, later.

31:52.143 --> 31:53.377
- Honey, can we take a break for
a minute?

31:53.379 --> 31:55.312
- You know what, that is a great
idea.

31:55.314 --> 31:58.115
Everybody, let's take a break.

31:58.117 --> 32:00.183
- I gotta hit the head.

32:00.185 --> 32:02.352
- Sam, will you help
daddy set up the grill?

32:02.354 --> 32:03.220
- Yeah, sure.

32:03.222 --> 32:04.222
- Thank you.

32:16.268 --> 32:19.102
- So are you grillin'
today or...?

32:43.695 --> 32:46.330
- All right, what's next?

32:46.332 --> 32:48.732
- I've got coleslaw in the
fridge

32:48.734 --> 32:50.701
and a bowl in that drawer.

32:50.703 --> 32:52.636
- All right.

32:53.604 --> 32:55.005
- Maggie, you need anything?

32:55.007 --> 32:56.206
- No.

32:59.978 --> 33:03.180
- Hm.

33:04.182 --> 33:05.382
- Hm?

33:06.417 --> 33:09.186
- No, I was just, I just said,
"hm."

33:09.188 --> 33:14.057
It was interesting what kind
of potato salad you're making.

33:14.059 --> 33:16.326
- What's that mean?

33:16.328 --> 33:16.326
- Doesn't mean anything,

33:16.328 --> 33:21.732
it just means it's interesting,
all right?

33:21.734 --> 33:24.468
What are you puttin' in it?

33:24.470 --> 33:27.471
- It's an all-mustard potato
salad.

33:30.041 --> 33:31.041
- Mustard?

33:31.609 --> 33:33.043
- That's right.

33:33.045 --> 33:34.644
- No, no mayonnaise?

33:39.317 --> 33:40.517
- That's right.

33:40.519 --> 33:41.718
No mayonnaise.

33:41.788 --> 33:42.687
- Why?

33:42.688 --> 33:42.686
- 'Cause I don't like
mayonnaise.

33:42.688 --> 33:48.125
- Well, but you always make
potato salad with mayonnaise.

33:48.127 --> 33:50.227
- Well, not this one.

33:50.229 --> 33:51.294
- All right.

33:51.571 --> 33:52.530
And why is that?

33:52.531 --> 33:56.366
Is that because of health or
something?

33:56.368 --> 33:59.603
Because I read somewhere that
mayonnaise is just as healthy

33:59.605 --> 34:00.804
as an avocado.

34:03.041 --> 34:05.342
- I don't know about that, mom.

34:05.344 --> 34:08.411
- I just never liked the stuff.

34:08.414 --> 34:10.313
- That's good to know, yeah?

34:10.315 --> 34:11.315
- Yeah.

34:12.717 --> 34:13.717
Oh.

34:15.085 --> 34:16.786
Oh, that's just great.

34:16.789 --> 34:20.724
So we're gonna have
potato salad with mustard.

34:22.393 --> 34:23.527
That's dandy.

34:25.063 --> 34:28.665
- I guess you just
prefer the devil's sperm.

34:28.667 --> 34:29.667
- What?

34:31.202 --> 34:33.070
What did you just say?

34:33.072 --> 34:34.304
- The devil's sperm.

34:34.306 --> 34:35.572
- Oh my god.

34:35.574 --> 34:38.241
- You prefer the devil's sperm?

34:38.243 --> 34:39.409
- You're disgusting.

34:41.780 --> 34:42.780
Jesus.

34:47.150 --> 34:48.085
My god.

34:48.087 --> 34:52.621
Why do you ever let her
talk to me like that?

34:55.293 --> 34:56.293
- Maggie.

34:56.828 --> 34:58.628
- Oh, you devil you.

35:06.771 --> 35:08.472
- John?

35:08.474 --> 35:10.407
- I'll be right there.

35:12.210 --> 35:15.312
- Looks like someone salted her
pie.

35:15.314 --> 35:16.847
- Everything okay?

35:16.849 --> 35:19.249
- It could be anything.

35:19.251 --> 35:19.249
Hey, Aiden.

35:19.251 --> 35:21.618
Are you still out in coryell
county?

35:21.620 --> 35:23.620
- That's right, still there.

35:23.622 --> 35:27.224
I do most of my work out
of jonesboro these days.

35:27.226 --> 35:29.126
- Well, what are you doin' to
keep busy?

35:29.128 --> 35:31.795
- Same thing that's kept me
busy for the last 40 years,

35:31.797 --> 35:33.763
electrical work mostly.

35:33.765 --> 35:37.567
A little carpentry, odd
jobs here and there.

35:38.870 --> 35:40.470
- Oh, here we go.

35:41.606 --> 35:43.773
- We could certainly use a good
handyman

35:43.775 --> 35:45.308
up in the big d.

35:45.310 --> 35:48.678
The only thing I can manage
to change are my diapers.

35:48.680 --> 35:51.915
- And we pray that he remembers
to change 'em every day.

35:51.917 --> 35:53.250
- There we go, I knew it.

35:54.219 --> 35:55.852
- John, you still practice law?

35:55.854 --> 35:57.754
- He knows the license
plate of every ambulance

35:57.756 --> 35:59.189
in tarrant county.

35:59.191 --> 36:00.724
- Yeah, I'm still a partner.

36:00.726 --> 36:02.425
They haven't caught me yet.

36:02.427 --> 36:04.394
- What do you know about life
insurance?

36:04.396 --> 36:06.863
- I know if Maureen knew
how much money we had,

36:06.865 --> 36:08.865
she would have run me over years
ago.

36:10.536 --> 36:11.401
Why, what's up?

36:11.403 --> 36:11.401
What do ya need?

36:11.403 --> 36:16.540
- I, ah, I'm thinking of changing
our policy, age and all,

36:16.542 --> 36:20.744
but these regulations of
preexisting conditions and stuff.

36:22.547 --> 36:24.648
I was just wondering if you knew
someone

36:24.650 --> 36:26.516
- I could talk to.
- - Mom.

36:26.518 --> 36:28.218
Will you help me?

36:28.220 --> 36:30.820
- Ah, well I could email
you a couple of names.

36:30.822 --> 36:32.589
You just send me all of your
information

36:32.591 --> 36:33.924
and I'll do it when I get back.

36:33.926 --> 36:36.560
- If you don't mind,
yeah, that'd be great.

36:36.562 --> 36:37.761
- No, I'd like to do it.

36:37.763 --> 36:38.828
- Thank you, thank you.

36:38.830 --> 36:39.830
- Sure.

36:40.898 --> 36:43.967
Yeah, excuse me, guys, for a
minute.

36:47.939 --> 36:49.472
What's the problem, Maureen?

36:49.474 --> 36:50.874
- You won't believe what she
said to me.

36:50.876 --> 36:52.409
- Momma, please.
- Can't we just...

36:52.411 --> 36:53.777
- mom!

36:53.779 --> 36:55.445
Please.

36:55.447 --> 36:56.447
- Fine.

37:08.459 --> 37:13.330
- Look, look, look, look,
over there on that branch.

37:13.332 --> 37:14.731
- What is that, a bird?

37:14.733 --> 37:17.534
- That's a brown-headed cowbird.

37:18.636 --> 37:20.971
- Oh god, not this again.

37:20.973 --> 37:22.706
- What's a cowbird?

37:22.708 --> 37:25.408
- Well, a cowbird is a member
of the blackbird family

37:25.410 --> 37:27.844
and they've evolved to follow
around

37:27.846 --> 37:31.581
the herds of cows and sheep and
buffalos

37:31.583 --> 37:34.684
and it picks the ticks off of
their backs.

37:34.686 --> 37:36.353
- Wow, this is just like animal
planet.

37:36.355 --> 37:37.520
- There it is.

37:37.522 --> 37:39.589
- Keep goin', daddy.

37:39.591 --> 37:41.992
- She's a brood parasite.

37:41.994 --> 37:43.326
- What's a brood parasite?

37:43.328 --> 37:45.028
- Ah ha, see, the curiosity of
youth.

37:45.030 --> 37:50.500
A brood parasite, see that's
when the female cowbird

37:50.502 --> 37:53.436
lays her eggs in the nest
of other birds, right.

37:53.438 --> 37:55.438
- So they make the
other birds raise their babies?

37:55.440 --> 37:56.339
- Exactly.

37:56.341 --> 37:57.341
- Hey!

37:57.908 --> 38:00.343
What're you sayin'?

38:00.345 --> 38:03.280
- Maggie, he didn't mean
anything.

38:11.055 --> 38:12.422
- God, that's, I'm sorry,

38:12.424 --> 38:13.823
I didn't mean anything really by
it.

38:13.825 --> 38:14.958
- I know.

38:14.960 --> 38:17.761
She'll be all right, just let
her go.

38:17.763 --> 38:21.831
Probably best to just
leave her alone for a bit.

38:25.670 --> 38:26.670
- Sorry.

38:28.939 --> 38:31.641
- Aren't you proud of yourself?

38:44.655 --> 38:45.522
- Hey.

38:45.524 --> 38:46.524
- Hey.

38:47.825 --> 38:50.727
- Come back down and join us.

38:50.729 --> 38:51.761
- Nnh.

38:51.763 --> 38:54.064
I lost my appetite.

38:54.066 --> 38:55.732
- Daddy didn't mean anything.

38:55.734 --> 38:57.500
He has really been into birds.

38:57.502 --> 39:00.537
We got him this book last
Christmas.

39:03.375 --> 39:05.375
I wasn't hungry anyway.

39:11.482 --> 39:12.982
- How are you?

39:12.984 --> 39:15.085
- Fine.

39:15.087 --> 39:16.553
- The hospital?

39:17.688 --> 39:20.523
- Took in a couple of extra
shifts.

39:20.525 --> 39:22.859
I'm workin' six days a week.

39:25.529 --> 39:27.464
- Busy's good.

39:27.466 --> 39:28.798
- Yeah, I guess.

39:31.502 --> 39:32.769
- I'm busy too.

39:33.571 --> 39:35.538
I had a few gallery showings

39:35.540 --> 39:36.840
and a couple new commissions.

39:36.842 --> 39:38.942
- That's nice, real nice.

39:40.511 --> 39:44.714
- A lot of hard work but...

39:45.716 --> 39:47.517
- But what?

39:48.886 --> 39:51.087
- Why'd you stop painting?

39:52.423 --> 39:53.423
- Oh.

39:55.993 --> 39:57.961
Well, I never had the time

39:57.963 --> 40:00.997
or the means to do anything with
it.

40:00.999 --> 40:03.666
I was so busy at the hospital.

40:05.903 --> 40:09.506
I just had a whole lotta things
goin' on.

40:11.709 --> 40:13.009
- I'm sorry.

40:13.011 --> 40:14.878
- For what?

40:14.880 --> 40:16.446
- Well, didn't you love it?

40:16.448 --> 40:19.549
- Hrmph, love has nothing
to do with it, Shannon.

40:19.551 --> 40:21.751
I do what I do to survive.

40:21.753 --> 40:22.852
- I didn't mean...

40:22.854 --> 40:23.853
- What?

40:23.855 --> 40:26.055
What are you talkin' about?

40:26.057 --> 40:29.793
- I just was, was just trying to
talk.

40:29.795 --> 40:31.594
- Talk about what?

40:31.596 --> 40:33.596
- I was just tryin' to,

40:34.698 --> 40:36.199
I really don't know you

40:36.201 --> 40:38.735
or anything about your life, my
father...

40:38.737 --> 40:39.969
- Shannon?

40:39.971 --> 40:42.639
I don't want to talk about it.

40:44.041 --> 40:47.710
Besides it's really none of your
business.

40:48.913 --> 40:51.080
- What do you mean?

40:51.082 --> 40:55.618
- Ahh, well, I see where
this is goin', mm-hmm.

40:55.620 --> 40:58.621
Next thing you're gonna tell me

40:58.623 --> 41:01.458
I'm the one that ruined your
life.

41:01.460 --> 41:02.460
Hm?

41:03.127 --> 41:05.595
- You don't get it, do you?

41:08.899 --> 41:12.569
I was nine years old when
i had my first sleepover,

41:12.571 --> 41:17.073
and it was great, until
it was time to go to bed.

41:17.075 --> 41:20.810
I was just lying there,
thinkin', worrying,

41:22.112 --> 41:23.480
that no one was going to come
back

41:23.482 --> 41:26.549
and pick me up in the morning.

41:26.551 --> 41:28.785
My friend's mother found me
in the middle of the night,

41:28.787 --> 41:28.785
crying in a corner.

41:28.787 --> 41:33.623
She had to call my parents
to come pick me up.

41:35.060 --> 41:37.660
So it's my fault that you
couldn't spend the night

41:37.662 --> 41:39.662
at your friend's house?

41:39.664 --> 41:42.031
- I stood in the front
door in my nightgown

41:42.033 --> 41:44.033
for my parents to come.

41:45.035 --> 41:47.837
I didn't think they were coming.

41:49.573 --> 41:51.708
But, of course, they did.

41:56.146 --> 41:59.082
- So it's all about you, isn't
it?

42:02.953 --> 42:03.953
Well...

42:06.590 --> 42:09.192
I was 17, thought I was in love,

42:12.162 --> 42:16.799
and I got pregnant and i
didn't want to have a baby.

42:16.801 --> 42:20.870
Your father blamed me for
it, so did my parents.

42:22.706 --> 42:26.910
No, I didn't want to have you,
but I didn't have a choice.

42:30.648 --> 42:31.948
And when I gave you up,

42:31.950 --> 42:35.285
you weren't supposed to come
back, ever.

42:36.820 --> 42:38.888
I moved on with my life.

42:42.059 --> 42:43.726
Do you understand?

42:47.831 --> 42:50.133
This has nothin' to do with
love.

42:50.135 --> 42:54.337
This has nothin' to do with
whether I loved you or not.

42:55.906 --> 42:58.841
The truth is, the day you were
born

42:58.843 --> 43:01.811
was the worst day of my life,

43:01.813 --> 43:04.681
'cause I wasn't ready to grow
up.

43:12.856 --> 43:14.791
- Sorry you feel that way.

43:14.793 --> 43:17.961
- I shouldn't be judged for
being honest.

43:17.963 --> 43:18.963
- No.

43:20.097 --> 43:21.097
Not at all.

43:22.766 --> 43:24.367
You are who you are.

44:41.945 --> 44:45.281
- All right, here we go!

44:45.283 --> 44:47.817
- Honey, could you give
me a minute so I could

44:47.819 --> 44:51.454
run into the little ladies'
room and check my face?

44:51.456 --> 44:55.858
- That's right, you're the
only one in this damn picture.

44:58.862 --> 45:01.130
- It is not a picture, it is a
portrait.

45:01.132 --> 45:04.000
It is a family portrait.

45:04.002 --> 45:05.768
Now, I think it means a
great deal to Shannon,

45:05.770 --> 45:08.705
so I think we should all look
our best.

45:08.707 --> 45:08.705
- No, you're right, Maureen.

45:08.707 --> 45:11.240
Your face could use some more
work.

45:11.242 --> 45:12.709
- Maggie, give
it a break, will ya?

45:12.711 --> 45:14.477
- Just shut your face.

45:14.479 --> 45:16.079
- I hit a nerve, did I?

45:16.081 --> 45:18.414
- Dammit, that's enough!

45:18.416 --> 45:21.050
Maybe we should all stop
thinking about ourselves

45:21.052 --> 45:25.254
for a few minutes and try
to remember why we're here.

45:26.290 --> 45:29.225
- I think that's a very good
idea.

45:35.766 --> 45:38.434
- And I thought
pork chop hill was bad.

46:00.190 --> 46:04.060
- Ugh, you would not
believe what's goin' on.

46:05.095 --> 46:06.863
Naw, we're all out there
posin' for the portrait,

46:06.865 --> 46:08.231
and my grandma starts pickin' a
fight

46:08.233 --> 46:10.032
with my mom's real mom.

46:10.034 --> 46:11.034
Classic.

46:12.836 --> 46:14.270
They did not trade blows.

46:14.272 --> 46:17.106
That would have been cool.

46:17.108 --> 46:20.910
Yeah, yeah, I'll be out
there in about 20 minutes.

46:20.912 --> 46:23.479
Mm-hmm, yeah, we passed it on
the way in.

46:23.481 --> 46:25.181
I'll meet ya there.

46:25.183 --> 46:26.449
All right, bye.

46:39.163 --> 46:40.163
- So...

46:44.201 --> 46:46.068
How you doin', honey?

46:47.871 --> 46:50.206
- I'm starting to think
this weekend was a mistake.

46:50.208 --> 46:52.575
- No, it wasn't a mistake.

46:52.577 --> 46:54.310
The guest list was a mistake.

46:54.312 --> 46:54.310
- Mom.

46:54.312 --> 46:56.078
- Oh, she's a hateful woman.

46:56.080 --> 46:57.080
- Mom, god!

46:59.349 --> 47:01.050
It's not about you.

47:01.052 --> 47:03.953
- I know it was your decision,

47:03.955 --> 47:06.489
but I think you could be a
little bit more understanding

47:06.491 --> 47:09.192
about the other people around
here.

47:09.194 --> 47:12.495
I mean, your daddy and Sam,
Liam, me...

47:12.497 --> 47:14.997
- are you saying I'm
not being sympathetic?

47:14.999 --> 47:17.200
- No, I'm not saying that.

47:18.569 --> 47:22.338
You convinced yourself
that this was gonna be

47:22.340 --> 47:25.274
one big happy family this
weekend.

47:26.410 --> 47:28.044
I mean, w-we've talked about
this.

47:28.046 --> 47:29.378
You do it a lot.

47:30.314 --> 47:33.282
You make up your mind
and then the doors close

47:33.284 --> 47:37.420
and the lock is locked and
nobody can get in anym...

47:37.422 --> 47:39.488
- maybe I don't want anyone in!

47:39.490 --> 47:41.023
Do you ever think about that?

47:41.025 --> 47:43.359
Maybe I just want to fit in,

47:44.461 --> 47:46.295
something I've been trying
to do since the fifth grade

47:46.297 --> 47:49.632
and those fucking, fucking
family trees.

47:52.302 --> 47:53.302
- Whew.

47:55.272 --> 47:58.474
Well, you know you were
four-weeks-old

48:00.644 --> 48:04.113
when your daddy and I brought
you home.

48:06.183 --> 48:10.386
I remember asking the woman
at the adoption agency

48:12.256 --> 48:13.656
what I should do,

48:13.658 --> 48:18.961
and she said, "oh, you just
take her home and you love her."

48:20.264 --> 48:24.467
Well, that sure wasn't enough.

48:26.470 --> 48:29.005
Can't tell you how long
it took for me to feel

48:31.242 --> 48:34.977
adequate and not guilty
for taking you away

48:38.482 --> 48:40.249
from another woman,

48:40.251 --> 48:43.519
a woman who happened to be your
mother.

48:47.624 --> 48:49.292
Dammit, I knew it.

48:50.961 --> 48:54.630
I knew when you were
young that at some point

48:55.699 --> 49:00.403
you were gonna go out and
you would try to find her.

49:00.405 --> 49:02.605
That real mother of yours.

49:07.577 --> 49:09.645
Oh god, I was so scared,

49:11.515 --> 49:15.718
so scared that you'd love
her more than you love me.

49:31.702 --> 49:32.635
- Hey, Liam.

49:32.637 --> 49:34.170
Where ya headed?

49:34.972 --> 49:37.139
- Goin' for a run.

49:37.141 --> 49:40.109
- Yeah, I guess we both
needed to get out of there

49:40.111 --> 49:41.577
for a little bit.

49:41.579 --> 49:44.113
- What's goin' on with them,
dad?

49:44.115 --> 49:45.614
Why they fightin' over mom?

49:45.616 --> 49:48.284
- It's complicated.

49:48.286 --> 49:49.685
- It's just weird.

49:49.687 --> 49:51.587
Why can't they just get along
anyways?

49:51.589 --> 49:53.522
- That would be great.

49:54.324 --> 49:56.459
They just don't see it that way.

49:56.461 --> 49:59.328
- Well, at least I got some good
photos.

49:59.330 --> 49:59.328
They're even smiling in some,

49:59.330 --> 50:02.765
so guess they got along okay,
right?

50:02.767 --> 50:07.036
- Yeah, a picture's
worth a thousand words, right?

50:07.038 --> 50:08.571
- Yeah, I guess so.

50:10.340 --> 50:14.643
- Do you know why people
smile in pictures?

50:14.645 --> 50:17.380
Because we tell 'em to.

50:17.382 --> 50:21.650
You can tell somebody to
smile and say "cheese,"

50:21.652 --> 50:25.054
but you can't really fake being
happy.

50:25.689 --> 50:30.092
Your mom, she's just, she's
trying to figure it all out.

50:31.528 --> 50:34.663
You know, find a way to be
happy.

50:34.665 --> 50:36.465
Or at least content.

50:40.337 --> 50:41.804
- Mom's not happy?

50:46.676 --> 50:48.677
- It's not that simple.

50:50.614 --> 50:52.548
Sometimes she's happy.

50:53.750 --> 50:58.154
She's trying to
connect with her past.

50:59.289 --> 51:03.092
Trying to connect with
her past and present.

51:04.194 --> 51:06.695
She wants to find out where she
came from

51:06.697 --> 51:09.698
so that she understands who she
is.

51:13.070 --> 51:15.271
Life isn't just a picture.

51:16.106 --> 51:19.675
It's a series of events
all strung together,

51:22.579 --> 51:26.649
like a puzzle, but no
matter how hard she tries,

51:31.121 --> 51:33.823
she may never find all the
pieces.

51:35.792 --> 51:39.829
And let's face it, women
have more pieces than men.

51:43.101 --> 51:46.102
- I think I'm gonna take off.

51:46.104 --> 51:47.536
- I don't blame ya.

51:47.538 --> 51:48.538
Hey, Liam?

51:50.474 --> 51:52.875
You got your cellphone on ya?

51:54.344 --> 51:57.413
All right, don't stay gone too
long.

52:07.591 --> 52:08.757
- All right, let's play ball!

52:08.759 --> 52:11.760
- All right, let's go it.

52:13.330 --> 52:15.764
- Now you see close only
counts in horseshoes...

52:17.435 --> 52:18.434
And hand grenades!

52:18.436 --> 52:19.301
- Hey!

52:19.303 --> 52:20.436
- Right, pop?

52:23.340 --> 52:25.508
- He was in the Korean war.

52:25.510 --> 52:27.443
- Wow, what was that like?

52:27.445 --> 52:29.411
- It was like a beautiful
picnic,

52:29.413 --> 52:30.479
set on fire.

52:55.873 --> 52:56.873
- Nice shot!

54:15.852 --> 54:17.419
- Franny?

54:17.421 --> 54:18.654
Stay awake.

54:20.291 --> 54:21.291
Hey!

54:22.292 --> 54:23.926
- I'm so hungry I could eat the
ass out

54:23.928 --> 54:25.427
of a low-flying duck.

54:26.297 --> 54:26.295
Oh, great.

54:26.297 --> 54:26.295
Well, have a seat and you two
are gonna sit next to franny.

54:26.297 --> 54:31.333
- Can I get anybody
else a drink while I'm up?

54:31.335 --> 54:33.836
Hey pops, I got you a
bourbon and water, all right?

54:33.838 --> 54:36.305
- Ah, you talked me into it.

54:36.307 --> 54:37.806
- For the love of Pete!

54:37.808 --> 54:40.376
Who made this Shepherd's pie?

54:40.378 --> 54:41.043
- Wow.

54:41.045 --> 54:42.411
- Team effort.

54:42.413 --> 54:44.280
- I was part of the team!

54:44.282 --> 54:46.915
- I watched while they made it.

54:46.917 --> 54:49.685
Hey, can you help me
out and bring it over?

54:49.687 --> 54:51.420
- Oh, sure.

54:54.824 --> 54:56.892
- Oh, I can smell it from here.

54:56.894 --> 54:56.892
Look at that.

54:56.894 --> 54:58.627
- Looks delicious.

54:58.629 --> 54:59.495
- Oh, that looks good.

54:59.497 --> 55:00.497
- Ooh!

55:02.432 --> 55:03.399
- There we go, Aiden.

55:03.401 --> 55:04.401
- All right.

55:05.803 --> 55:08.370
I would like to make a toast.

55:11.007 --> 55:13.042
Thank you all for coming.

55:13.044 --> 55:14.977
I know I've thrown you some
curveballs.

55:14.979 --> 55:16.979
- Some curveballs?

55:16.981 --> 55:19.815
- It's not what you were
expecting,

55:19.817 --> 55:22.484
but I've been thinking about
this weekend

55:22.486 --> 55:24.553
for a long time.

55:24.555 --> 55:27.089
It's been a dream of mine

55:27.091 --> 55:30.426
and the gifts you have brought,

55:30.428 --> 55:32.795
they meant a lot to me.

55:32.797 --> 55:34.930
So, thank you and cheers.

55:35.832 --> 55:36.699
- Cheers.

55:36.701 --> 55:37.701
- Cheers.

55:42.505 --> 55:46.008
- If it's okay, I'd
like to read something.

55:47.444 --> 55:50.846
It's a letter I sent home to
your grandma

55:51.815 --> 55:53.749
from the war in Korea.

55:55.819 --> 55:57.753
It was pork chop hill.

56:02.759 --> 56:04.960
"Good morning, darling."

56:04.962 --> 56:06.895
"Here is another day without
you,"

56:06.897 --> 56:11.567
"but nevertheless, you
are forever on my mind."

56:11.569 --> 56:14.503
"Yesterday I received your
letter."

56:14.505 --> 56:17.840
"You'll never know how happy
that made me."

56:17.842 --> 56:22.678
"It gave me new life and
new strength to carry on."

56:22.680 --> 56:24.446
"This is the first
chance I've had to write"

56:24.448 --> 56:28.117
"since we staged an attack in
two villages"

56:28.119 --> 56:30.652
"in the high mountain."

56:30.654 --> 56:34.723
"We fought all day and
only advanced a few miles"

56:35.692 --> 56:39.928
"and we paid for it dearly
with blood and lives."

56:39.930 --> 56:42.131
"I was in a daze for most of it,"

56:42.133 --> 56:45.734
"with a prayer and your name on
my lips."

56:45.736 --> 56:47.569
"Every step I took I thought of
you,"

56:47.571 --> 56:51.573
"and about our time when
we would be together soon."

56:51.575 --> 56:54.076
"At present, I have 12
men under my command"

56:54.078 --> 56:57.946
"and we're guarding 80 enemy
prisoners."

56:57.948 --> 56:59.581
"This'll all be over soon,"

56:59.583 --> 57:03.852
"and I'll be on my way
home to your loving arms."

57:03.854 --> 57:06.755
"I love you more than the words
of this letter can express."

57:06.757 --> 57:09.491
"Your loving husband, Francis."

57:12.095 --> 57:14.897
I brought this for you, sweetie.

57:22.639 --> 57:24.640
- I love you.

57:27.444 --> 57:29.144
- Would you mind
if I said a blessing?

57:29.146 --> 57:30.146
- Please.

57:34.083 --> 57:37.553
- Bless, o lord, this
food we are about to eat

57:37.555 --> 57:39.855
and we pray you, god, that it
will be good

57:39.857 --> 57:41.790
for our body and soul.

57:42.792 --> 57:47.696
And if there be any poor
creatures hungry or thirsty

57:47.698 --> 57:49.698
walking along the road,

57:50.667 --> 57:54.803
send them in to us that we
could share this food with them,

57:54.805 --> 57:58.640
just as you share your
gifts with all of us.

57:58.642 --> 57:59.675
Amen.

57:59.677 --> 58:02.644
- Amen.
- - Amen.

58:02.646 --> 58:03.712
- All right!

58:04.647 --> 58:06.248
Where are you going?

58:08.585 --> 58:09.251
Ah.

58:09.253 --> 58:10.719
- Dun-dun-dah!

58:11.889 --> 58:14.089
All right, all right, everybody
smile.

58:14.091 --> 58:15.091
- Okay.

58:17.527 --> 58:18.527
- Smile, c'mon!

58:24.834 --> 58:26.001
- All right!

58:26.003 --> 58:29.271
Now who would like some
Shepherd's pie?

58:30.740 --> 58:32.241
All right, you're gonna
have to pass your plates.

58:32.243 --> 58:33.509
It's too hot.

58:33.511 --> 58:35.611
- This looks fantastic.

58:35.613 --> 58:38.113
- Want some butter?

58:38.115 --> 58:39.115
Thank you.

58:39.949 --> 58:41.049
- You want some bread?

58:41.051 --> 58:42.217
- I think I'm gonna...

58:42.219 --> 58:44.620
- This is so good.

58:45.522 --> 58:49.625
- Could someone pass
me some bread, please?

58:49.627 --> 58:50.993
- Oh, sure.

58:50.995 --> 58:52.828
- Would you like some butter?

58:52.830 --> 58:53.695
- There we go.

58:53.697 --> 58:54.897
- There we go.

58:54.899 --> 58:57.266
- And me too.

58:57.268 --> 58:59.101
Pass it down.

58:59.103 --> 59:01.003
- I'd like some more whiskey.

59:01.005 --> 59:01.870
Is that okay?

59:01.872 --> 59:02.738
- Sure.

59:02.740 --> 59:04.206
- Me too.

59:06.175 --> 59:07.175
- Trade ya.

59:10.213 --> 59:12.080
Get this stuff off of...

59:12.082 --> 59:13.815
- Oh, that smells so good,
darling.

59:13.817 --> 59:13.815
- There ya go.

59:13.817 --> 59:18.186
- Liam, did you know that
Maggie was quite a dancer

59:18.188 --> 59:19.188
in her day?

59:20.023 --> 59:21.156
- Maggie?

59:21.158 --> 59:22.291
A dancer?

59:22.293 --> 59:23.725
I didn't know that.

59:23.727 --> 59:25.627
I wouldn't have known
that in a million years.

59:25.629 --> 59:27.162
- So you danced?

59:27.164 --> 59:29.631
- Oh yeah, as a girl I did,

59:33.036 --> 59:34.036
a little.

59:35.738 --> 59:39.207
We went on a tour a little bit
one summer.

59:40.944 --> 59:44.146
- Liam darling, would you
pass the salt and pepper?

59:44.148 --> 59:45.614
- There you go.

59:45.616 --> 59:47.816
